## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1️⃣ Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/resume-screening.git
cd resume-screening

2️⃣ Create Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv

Activate:

Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate
Mac/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

3️⃣ Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4️⃣ Add API Key
Create .env file:
GROQ_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

5️⃣ Add Resume PDFs
Place resumes inside:

data/
6️⃣ Run Application
streamlit run app.py

💬 Usage
Enter recruiter-style queries like:

"Python developer with machine learning experience"
"AWS cloud engineer with 3+ years experience"
"Fresher with NLP skills"
🧠 How It Works
1. Resume Parsing
PDFs are loaded using LangChain
Text is extracted and split into chunks
2. Embeddings
Each chunk is converted into vector embeddings using Sentence Transformers
3. Vector Search
FAISS indexes embeddings
Query is converted to vector and matched with resumes
4. LLM Response
Top results are passed to LLM
LLM generates:
Best candidates
Matching skills

Explanation:
🧪 Sample Queries
Query	Expected Result
Python ML developer	Rahul, Neha
Data analyst with experience	Amit
Java backend developer	Priya
AWS engineer	Arjun

⚠️ Limitations
Basic resume parsing (no structured extraction yet)
No persistent database (FAISS stored locally)
Limited ranking logic (can be improved)
No authentication or user roles